          "formulaExpression": "(100x + y) - 542 = 6(100y + x)",
          "calculation": "100x + y - 542 = 600y + 6x \\Rightarrow 94x - 599y = 542",
          "result": ""
        },
        {
          "stepNumber": 3,
          "explanation": "Rearrange: $94x = 542 + 599y$, so $x = \\frac{542 + 599y}{94} = 5 + \\frac{72 + 129y}{94}$. For x to be an integer, (72 + 129y) must be divisible by 94.",
          "formula": null,
          "formulaExpression": "x = 5 + \\frac{72 + 129y}{94}",
          "calculation": "Try y = 6: 72 + 129 \\times 6 = 72 + 774 = 846 = 9 \\times 94. \\quad x = 5 + 9 = 44.",
          "result": "x = 44 (but paise must be < 100, so check: y=6 is valid)"
        },
        {
          "stepNumber": 4,
          "explanation": "Correct cheque amount = x rupees y paise = 6 rupees 44 paise = ₹6.44 (since written cheque was 44 rupees 6 paise, correct is 6 rupees 44 paise).",
          "formula": null,
          "formulaExpression": "",
          "calculation": "",
          "result": "₹6.44"
        }
      ],
      "shortcut": "",
      "commonMistake": "Confusing which is the written amount and which is the correct amount after transposition.",
      "timeToSolve": "120 seconds"
    },
